#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/integration-testing-using-virtual-machines.md:0
msgid "Re-running successful tests"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/integration-testing-using-virtual-machines.md:225
msgid ""
"<!-- FIXME: this should be a separate recipe that can be linked to, as it's "
"a bit of knowledge one will need now and again. -->\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/integration-testing-using-virtual-machines.md:227
msgid ""
"Because test results are kept in the Nix store, a successful test is cached. "
"This means that Nix will not run the test a second time as long as the test "
"setup (node configuration and test script) stays semantically the same. "
"Therefore, to run a test again, one needs to remove the result."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/integration-testing-using-virtual-machines.md:231
msgid ""
"If you would try to delete the result using the symbolic link, you will get "
"the following error:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/integration-testing-using-virtual-machines.md:233
msgid "nix-store --delete ./result\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/integration-testing-using-virtual-machines.md:237
msgid ""
"finding garbage collector roots...\n"
"0 store paths deleted, 0.00 MiB freed\n"
"error: Cannot delete path '/nix/store/4klj06bsilkqkn6h2sia8dcsi72wbcfl-vm-"
"test-run-unnamed' since it is still alive. To find out why, use: nix-store --"
"query --roots\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/integration-testing-using-virtual-machines.md:241
msgid ""
"Instead, remove the symbolic link and only then remove the cached result:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/integration-testing-using-virtual-machines.md:243
msgid ""
"rm ./result\n"
"nix-store --delete /nix/store/4klj06bsilkqkn6h2sia8dcsi72wbcfl-vm-test-run-"
"unnamed\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/integration-testing-using-virtual-machines.md:248
msgid "This can be also done with one command:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/integration-testing-using-virtual-machines.md:250
msgid ""
"result=$(readlink -f ./result) rm ./result && nix-store --delete $result\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/integration-testing-using-virtual-machines.md:255
msgid "Tests with multiple virtual machines"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/integration-testing-using-virtual-machines.md:257
msgid ""
"Tests can involve multiple virtual machines, for example to test client-"
"server-communication."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/integration-testing-using-virtual-machines.md:259
msgid "The following example setup includes:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/integration-testing-using-virtual-machines.md:260
msgid ""
"A virtual machine named `server` running [nginx](https://nginx.org/en/) with "
"default configuration."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/integration-testing-using-virtual-machines.md:261
msgid ""
"A virtual machine named `client` that has `curl` available to make an HTTP "
"request."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/integration-testing-using-virtual-machines.md:262
msgid ""
"A `testScript` orchestrating testing logic between `client` and `server`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/integration-testing-using-virtual-machines.md:264
msgid ""
"The complete `client-server-test.nix` file content looks like the following:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/integration-testing-using-virtual-machines.md:266
msgid ""
"let\n"
"  nixpkgs = fetchTarball \"https://github.com/NixOS/nixpkgs/tarball/"
"nixos-23.11\";\n"
"  pkgs = import nixpkgs { config = {}; overlays = []; };\n"
"in\n"
"\n"
"pkgs.testers.runNixOSTest {\n"
"  name = \"client-server-test\";\n"
"\n"
"  nodes.server = { pkgs, ... }: {\n"
"    networking = {\n"
"      firewall = {\n"
"        allowedTCPPorts = [ 80 ];\n"
"      };\n"
"    };\n"
"    services.nginx = {\n"
"      enable = true;\n"
"      virtualHosts.\"server\" = {};\n"
"    };\n"
"  };\n"
"\n"
"  nodes.client = { pkgs, ... }: {\n"
"    environment.systemPackages = with pkgs; [\n"
"      curl\n"
"    ];\n"
"  };\n"
"\n"
"  testScript = ''\n"
"    server.wait_for_unit(\"default.target\")\n"
"    client.wait_for_unit(\"default.target\")\n"
"    client.succeed(\"curl http://server/ | grep -o \\\"Welcome to nginx!\\"
"\"\")\n"
"  '';\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

